reviews.text: I am a fan of Tam Jai and have been to other shops. This was my first time here at this location. They really need to fix the hygiene. There's hair in my noodle soup, I was disgusted and wanted to leave. They offered me another bowl of noodle soup and guess what! There's hair in it too. Shocking. I won't come to this shop again.
Soup base is great. Tons of flavour and white pepper. All the sides I've tried are also tasty. The century egg is a must!
Not a bad option for a rush and quick lunch
Tasty n value for money
The taste of food is going bad from time to time....this is probably the last time visiting the restaurant
